-- CCB, China Eastern, Henderson Land, Li & Fung: Hong Kong Equities Preview
-- Ronnie Koo
-- 2010-07-09T01:15:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/ccb-china-eastern-henderson-land-li-fung-hong-kong-equities-preview.html

          
          
             The  following  companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  
 The  Hang Seng Index  rose 1 percent to 20,050.56.  The Hang
Seng China Enterprises Index , which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, climbed 0.6 percent to 11,375.29.  
 China Construction Bank Corp.  (939 HK): The company plans
to open 100 rural bank branches by the end of next year, the
21st Century Business Herald reported, citing an unidentified
person close to the bank. China’s second largest lender gained
0.2 percent to HK$6.21.  
 China Eastern Airlines Corp.  (670 HK): The airline’s
passenger numbers in June rose 70 percent from a year ago, China
Business News reported, citing a company statement. The shares
rose 1.9 percent to HK$3.27.  
 Henderson Land Development Co.  (12 HK): The developer
controlled by billionaire  Lee Shau-kee  has declined an
invitation to appear at Hong Kong’s Legislative Council next
week to answer lawmakers’ questions related to failed sales of
luxury apartments at its 39 Conduit Road. The stock climbed 0.6
percent to HK$46.05.  
 Li & Fung Ltd.  (494 HK): The biggest supplier to retailers
including Wal-Mart Stores Inc. paid about $140 million for
health & beauty, jeans and fashion companies. Li & Fung also
signed four licensing deals in the “last few months,” it said
in a statement yesterday. The stock advanced 1.9 percent to
HK$35.20.  
